, to be construed as creating new mandate on any party regarding health insurance coverage, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/210/s203/f"},"text":"section 203(f) of Pub. L. 107–210","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Construction note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s35"},"text":"section 35 of Title 26","children":[],"tail":", Internal Revenue Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb67eb021-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Plan Amendments Not Required Until January 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions directing that if any amendments made by subtitle A or subtitle C of title XI [§§ 1101–1147 and 1171–1177] or title XVIII [§§ 1800–1899A] of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":" require an amendment to any plan, such plan amendment shall not be required to be made before the first plan year beginning on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s1140"},"text":"section 1140 of Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s401"},"text":"section 401 of Title 26","children":[],"tail":", Internal Revenue Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
